label.value: continuous framework

definition.value: Modelling approach where the quantities of participants are considered continuous, and represented by real values. The associated simulation methods make use of differential equations.

label.value: discrete framework

definition.value: Modelling approach where the quantities of participants are considered discrete, and represented by integer values. The associated simulation methods can be deterministic or stochastic.

label.value: mathematical expression

definition.value: Formal representation of a calculus linking parameters and variables of a model.

label.value: forward zeroth order rate constant, discrete case
